    "causal_summary": "The 005-memory-indexer-invariants deep review surfaced one release-blocker correctness gap (P1-001) and 13 advisory cleanup items (P2-001..P2-013). The P1 specifically: parser/discovery correctly exclude constitutional/README.md, but storage-layer mutation paths (checkpoint restore, SQL update, post-insert metadata, cleanup CLI) only check the broader `isConstitutionalPath()` predicate. A poisoned checkpoint or pre-existing DB row can therefore preserve a constitutional README as `importance_tier='constitutional'` even though normal ingestion would reject it. Hunter→Skeptic→Referee adversarial self-check confirmed P1 severity.",
